{"questionId":"9066239","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Benzoic acid, C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>5</sub>COOH, is another derivative of benzene.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Outline <strong>one</strong> piece of physical evidence for the structure of the benzene ring.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em>Any one of:</em></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">«regular» hexagon</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em><strong>OR</strong></em></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">all «H–C–C/C-C-C» angles equal/120º <strong>[✔]</strong><br>all C–C bond lengths equal/intermediate between double and single</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em><strong>OR</strong></em></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">bond order 1.5 <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066239","referenceCode":"19M.2.hl.TZ1.c","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Outline one piece of physical evidence for the structure of the benzene ring.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.1 Fundamentals of organic chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}